Package runner

Class WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner

java.lang.Object
org.jzy3d.analysis.AbstractAnalysis
runner.ScatterPlot
runner.WeatherScatterPlot
runner.WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.jzy3d.analysis.IAnalysis
public class WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner
extends WeatherScatterPlot
This class contains a runner used to display the 3d embedding of Polygons generated from the weather stations dataset.

Multiple embedding presets can be selected to view different interesting results. These presets are based on different Embedders and Measures.

Author:
Anton Ballmaier

  • Constructor Details

    • WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner

      public WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner​(WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner.Preset preset)
      Constructs a new WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner object using the given WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner.Preset for embedding. The point size of the embedded points is fixed to 5 since this dataset is quite small.
      Parameters:
      preset - the WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner.Preset defining the Embedder used to generate points from the dataset

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
      Main method making this class a runner for the scatter plot it implements.

      A WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner-Instance is initialized and used to plot the embedding of the weather station dataset. The used WeatherStationsScatterPlotRunner.Preset can be changed to view the different predefined embedding methods.

      Parameters:
      args - unused
